entry.title: Make sure fixed-length getComputedStyle() inset values roundtrip
entry.content:
Since crrev.com/c/4583533, when we try to get an inset value from an

absolutely positioned box, we always get it from the layout result.



This caused some rounding errors, since layout and CSS values have

different precisions. And this is unexpected to some sites.



This patch makes sure that we directly return result from the computed

style in simple cases (fixed-length values without position fallback

complications), so that the result roundtrips and avoids the rounding

difference.

entry.title: Add weak feature keyword to mojo
entry.content:
This CL adds a top-level keyword `feature` to mojo[0]. Unlike existing

keywords this token is used widely in existing mojo definitions

so it is not sensible to reserve this keyword - instead it is introduced

as a weak keyword - where it will be parsed as a feature token if

used as a top-level token (e.g. where mojo would expect to see

'interface', 'struct' etc.) but as a normal token in other places.



When used at the top level `feature` throws a parse error. Following

CLs will implement the use of the keyword to allow mojo to be

aware of runtime features. This CL mainly serves to add the

`name_wrapped` helper to the mojo parser, and isolates formatting

changes that result. Presubmit line length checks on parser.py

have been removed - python's lex/yacc modules use function level

comments when defining their grammar and wrapping these is awkward.



[0] https://docs.google.com/document/d/1kKFHu73SNwpBfPJzrVH2vLbpu9_1WuZhngFBqtJhwqw/edit?pli=1

entry.title: [Select to Speak] Inject clipboard copy in Lacros gdocs tabs
entry.content:
Select to speak tries to speak selected text with search+s,

and uses the a11y tree to determine the selection region. Google

docs does not populate selection on the underlying contenteditable

even when the canvas appears visually selected. As a work-around,

we fire a clipboard copy event from Select to Speak upon search+s

in gdocs and then paste the text within Select to Speak and

read the plain text. For more, see go/sts-selection-in-drive.



This change adds the workaround to Google docs in Lacros tabs,

where chrome.tabs in Ash wasn't able to find the tab or execute

the script. Now STS in Ash requests EmbeddedA11yHelper in Lacros

injects the content script via private extension APIs and

crosapi.



This does not have automated tests because it must be run on

live gdocs pages, and tests on CQ cannot have external

dependencies on gdocs. The original feature in Ash also lacks

automated tests. As a follow-up I will try to add tast tests

for Ash and Lacros.



in Google Docs

entry.title: [APS] Create and show tab cards on hover
entry.content:
This CL adds strip tab text hover card support, with the card containing

tab title and URL information. The CL broadly includes the following

updates:



- Create a new LinearLayout for the tab hover card.

- Determine the width of the hover card, that is subject to change based

on the window width. The hover card should not exceed 90% of the window

width and should always maintain an 8dp lateral margin relative to the

enclosing window.

- Determine the horizontal and vertical positions of the hover card with

respect to the hovered tab, while taking the folio/detached/GM2 tab

shapes and RTL layout into account.

- Update the background and text colors of the hover card based on the

theme and incognito mode.

entry.title: Add support for the "Priority" header for HTTP/2 and HTTP/3
entry.content:
This adds support for the Priority HTTP Header field from HTTP

Extensible Priorities (RFC 9218)

https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9218#name-the-priority-http-header-fi



The header is gated by the feature flag "PriorityHeader" which is disabled by default.



The core of the change is in 3 files:



spdy_http_utils.cc - Allows for an optional priority param to be provided when generating spdy-formatted headers from a request's HTTP headers.



spdy_http_stream.cc - Pass the request priority when generating the headers for a HTTP/2 request.



quic_http_stream.cc - Pass the request priority when generating the headers for a HTTP/3 request.



The rest of the changes are for plumbing the feature flag, defaulting to no priority header for non-request streams, parameterizing the impacted test suites to test with both the feature enabled and disabled and fixes to the test suites to generate the appropriate headers in both cases.

entry.title: Fix all-with-discrete transition test
entry.content:
Issues with the test:

* TransitionStart was being tested before confirming that the

animation was ready. The timing of when the animation is ready is

UA dependent.

* Waiting a single frame after starting the animation ensures the

transtionstart event is queued, but event dispatch could be in the

next frame



We can avoid the timing nuances by simply querying all animations.

The query itself forces a style update. The animation will be in

a play-pending state at this point so the transitionstart has not

had a chance to fire; however, we can verify that the animation is

a CSSTransition for the expected property.



This test still fails on Firefox, but that is due to not supporting

"allow-discrete". The test passes reliably in Chrome.

entry.title: Cancel AmbientUiLauncher::Initialize() when screen saver is closed.
entry.content:
This is a subtle case that was missed during implementation and

was surfaced by the DLC video migration, which has an asynchronous

initialization method. It's possible for screen saver to be closed

while there is still a pending Initialize() call. The initialization

callback should not be run in this case. It's currently not an issue

because we check that ambient mode is "visible" before creating

the widget. But it can lead to subtle issues in the future. All

pending tasks at all layers should be canceled when the screen

saver is stopped.
